# creative / openframeworks

openFrameworks creative-coding apps: a cross-platform C++/OpenGL toolkit driven by the `setup()`/`update()`/`draw()` loop. The native deliverable is a realtime graphics window; the portable shareable artifact is an Emscripten WebGL build (`index.html` + `.wasm` + `.js`) that runs in a canvas/iframe. This scaffold emits an editable `ofApp` (C++ source) plus a hosting `index.html`, and renders to WebGL via emsdk when present.

