## Required reading
- openFrameworks official documentation (canonical API; framework MIT) — https://openframeworks.cc/documentation/
- openFrameworks learning tutorials (official, CC/site) — https://openframeworks.cc/learning/
- openFrameworks Emscripten setup (official; the WebGL/HTML artifact path) — https://openframeworks.cc/setup/emscripten/
- openFrameworks GitHub source + README guides (official, MIT) — https://github.com/openframeworks/openFrameworks

## Render
```bash
# One-time core install (macOS):
git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/openframeworks/openFrameworks
cd openFrameworks/scripts/osx && ./download_libs.sh

# Browser (portable WebGL artifact) — needs emsdk + OF emscripten platform:
git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk && ./emsdk/emsdk install latest && ./emsdk/emsdk activate latest
source ./emsdk/emsdk_env.sh
# in the generated project dir, with platform=emscripten:
emmake make            # -> bin/index.html + .wasm + .js
python3 -m http.server 8000   # serve bin/, open http://localhost:8000

# Native (osx/linux) realtime window:
make -j4 && make RunRelease
# offline PNG: in ofApp::draw() add
#   ofImage img; img.grabScreen(0,0,ofGetWidth(),ofGetHeight()); img.save("out.png");
```

## Failure modes
- Missing `download_libs.sh` step — link errors against the precompiled OF core libs; run it before any build.
- Emscripten platform not configured — `emmake make` falls back to native target; follow https://openframeworks.cc/setup/emscripten/ and set the project's platform to emscripten.
- WebGL build serves blank — must be served over HTTP (not `file://`); `.wasm` MIME / CORS issues break the canvas.
- Fully headless on macOS is unsupported — needs a GL/window context; use the Vulkan renderer or Linux + XVFB for offline frame dumps.
- `ofImage::grabScreen` before the first frame draws produces an empty image; call it inside `draw()` after rendering.
